{"article_id":"SF0fcIph8XpdHaUN","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The US Supreme Court has ruled against the Trump administration 's policy","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"to deny asylum to any migrants","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"crossing the US-Mexico border illegally .","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"The top court rejected the policy 5-4 ,","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"with Chief Justice John Roberts siding with the court 's liberals .","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"Federal judges had previously stayed the asylum ban ,","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"ruling","depth":8},{"id":7,"text":"it tried to circumvent existing laws","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"granting anyone the right to asylum in the US .","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"The government had described the policy as a way","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"to address the border crisis .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"Conservative justices Neil Gorsuch , Clarence Thomas , Samuel Alito and Brett Kavanaugh dissented .","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"The court offered no opinion , just a document","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"noting the order","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"upholding the lower courts ' ruling against the ban .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"On 9 November , President Donald Trump issued a proclamation","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"stating","depth":9},{"id":17,"text":"that only asylum claims","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"made at official ports of entry","depth":11},{"id":19,"text":"would be heard .","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"Lower federal courts blocked the policy from going into effect soon after .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"In Solicitor General Noel Francisco 's request to the Supreme Court","depth":11},{"id":22,"text":"to give the proclamation the go-ahead ,","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"he claimed","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"the president 's decree was for border security","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"and to discourage dangerous crossings .","depth":10},{"id":26,"text":"The petition claimed","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"that migrants entered the US illegally","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"and then claimed asylum ,","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"allowing them to remain in the country","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"while their cases were being processed","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"- even if those cases were unlikely to be granted .","depth":9},{"id":32,"text":"`` These measures are designed","depth":9},{"id":33,"text":"to channel asylum seekers to ports of entry ,","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"where their claims can be processed in an orderly manner ;","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"deter unlawful and dangerous border crossings ;","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"and reduce the backlog of meritless asylum claims . ''","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"The government added","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"that the temporary ban would `` assist the president in sensitive and ongoing diplomatic negotiations '' with Mexico , El Salvador , Guatemala and Honduras .","depth":9},{"id":39,"text":"The American Civil Liberties Union","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"( ACLU ) ,","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"which issued the legal challenge to the ban ,","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"said","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"the policy was unjustifiable and unfair .","depth":7},{"id":44,"text":"The ACLU noted","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"that many legitimate asylum seekers ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"fearing for their lives ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"enter illegally `` through no fault of their own '' .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"`` The government 's statutory arguments boil down to the contention","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"that it would be more 'rational ' and 'sensible ' to deny asylum to people","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"who enter illegally .","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"But Congress expressly rejected that argument , ''","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"ACLU court documents stated .","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"The ACLU concluded","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"that the administration was addressing `` the wrong branch of government '' with its request .","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"`` It should make its case to Congress","depth":11},{"id":56,"text":"rather than seeking emergency intervention from this court","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"regarding an almost 40-year-old statute . ''","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"Though the administration 's ban was described as temporary ,","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"the lower courts ruled","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"that it was not up to the White House to change existing federal laws in this way .","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"Under US law , there is a legal obligation to hear asylum claims from migrants","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"if they say","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"they fear violence in their home countries -","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"regardless of how they have entered the country .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"US District Judge Jon Tigar in California had first blocked Mr Trump 's proclamation in November ,","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"and extended his order this month .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"Conservative Judge Jay Bybee wrote in the appeals opinion :","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"`` Just as we may not ,","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"as we are often reminded ,","depth":12},{"id":70,"text":"'legislate from the bench ,","depth":12},{"id":71,"text":"' neither may the Executive legislate from the Oval Office '' ,","depth":10},{"id":72,"text":"the Washington Post reported .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"The latest group of migrants","depth":6},{"id":74,"text":"seeking entry into the US","depth":6},{"id":75,"text":"come from across Central America .","depth":5},{"id":76,"text":"They travelled north for weeks in what Mr Trump described as a `` caravan of people '' .","depth":5},{"id":77,"text":"They say","depth":6},{"id":78,"text":"they are fleeing persecution , poverty and violence in their home countries of Honduras , Guatemala and El Salvador .","depth":6},{"id":79,"text":"In the run-up to the US mid-term elections , President Trump said","depth":4},{"id":80,"text":"most were criminals ,","depth":5},{"id":81,"text":"called the caravan an invasion ,","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"and ordered troops to the border .","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"On Thursday , the Department of Homeland Security announced","depth":3},{"id":84,"text":"that any migrants","depth":5},{"id":85,"text":"who illegally enter the US","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"- including asylum seekers -","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"will have to wait in Mexico","depth":5},{"id":88,"text":"for their cases to be heard .","depth":5},{"id":89,"text":"The Mexican government has said","depth":4},{"id":90,"text":"it will offer migrants work visas and protections","depth":5},{"id":91,"text":"while they await asylum proceedings ,","depth":5},{"id":92,"text":"according to the US Department of State .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":185,"left":175,"right":184,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":175,"left":165,"right":174,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":165,"left":107,"right":164,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":107,"left":97,"right":106,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":95,"right":96,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":95,"left":0,"right":94,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":94,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":106,"left":102,"right":105,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":102,"left":100,"right":101,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":5,"right":99,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":6,"right":98,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":98,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":9,"right":10,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":11,"right":104,"relation":"elabor